ğŸï¸ Carousel Behavior (Important Design Choices)

âœ… Why custom-slide Exists

Bootstrap does not control carousel height by default.

Height is controlled safely using a custom class, not Bootstrap core classes.

.custom-slide {

  height: 570px;

}



.custom-slide img {

  height: 100%;

  object-fit: cover;

}

âœ… Benefits

Prevents image distortion

Keeps full-width responsiveness

Avoids breaking Bootstrap carousel animation

Allows easy height changes from one place

âš ï¸ Critical Rules Followed

âœ” Never renamed carousel-item (required by Bootstrap JS)

âœ” Custom styling added via extra class, not replacement

âœ” Separate carousels avoid image scaling hacks

âœ” Uses Bootstrap display utilities instead of JavaScript hacks

ğŸ› ï¸ How to Customize

ğŸ”¹ Change Carousel Height

Edit one line:

.custom-slide {

  height: 570px;

}

ğŸ”¹ Make Height Responsive

.custom-slide {

  height: 250px;

}



@media (min-width: 768px) {

  .custom-slide {

    height: 570px;

  }

}

ğŸ”¹ Change Logo Size

.image {

  height: 50px;

  width: auto;

}

